questions_title:
Consider the following program written in pseudo-code. Assume that x and y are integers: 
Count (x, y) {
if (y ! = 1) {
if (x ! = 1) {
print(“*”);
Count (x/2, y);
}
else {
y = y – 1;
Count (1024, y);
}
}
}
The number of times that the print statement is executed by the call Count (1024, 1024) is 
__________.
